Exocrine pancreas, lymphoid and neuronal cells showed strong cytoplasmic positivity. Urinary bladder, testis, placenta and breast displayed moderate immunoreactivity. Remaining normal cells were weakly stained or negative.
Several cases of skin, urothelial cancer, malignant gliomas, lymphomas and melanomas displayed moderate immunoreactivity. Remaining malignancies were weakly stained or negative.
